<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2011-05-03</DATELINE><TITLE>The Clinical Definitions of Asthma</TITLE><BODY>It is believed that the term “asthma” was coined by Hippocrates around 450 bc. The term literally means “panting,” from the Greek. Descriptions of the clinical presentation of those affected with asthma appear in medical literature throughout history.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>